net.mwav.framework.mail

Class MessageBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.mwav.framework.mail.MessageBuilder

  • public class MessageBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    This class helps build a message briefly using method chaining.

    To send a message, an appropriate subclass of Message (e.g. MimeMessage) is instantiated,

    the attributes and content are filled in,

    and the message is sent using the Transport.send method.

    The default constructor is not allowed, since Session information is required to instant Message object.

    In order to build a Message :

    1. Call MessageBuilder(Properties) to instant MimeMessage.
    2. Call setter methods (e.g. #setRecipients(RecipientType, List)) to fill the attributes and content
    3. Call build() to get a Message.
    4. Call MailLib.send(Message) to send email.
    Since:
    1.0.4
    Version:
    v1.0
    Author:
    남동희
    See Also:
